> Who can resist tender, savory, hand-stuffed wontons? We're sending over everything you need to fold up a whole bunch of vegetarian corn wontons flavored with ginger and garlic and doused in a luscious, spicy coconut curry sauce dotted with tender green beans. Finish with a garnish of peanuts, cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice.

Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @corn{1}(drained and rinsed) - reserve 1/2 cup in a #medium bowl{}. Set aside for use in Step 3.

Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and cut into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{2%cloves}. (No need to mince or grate ginger or garlic; you will be blending these in Step 3!) Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary and cut into 1-inch pieces. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped) leaves and stems. Quarter @lime{1}. Crush @peanuts{1%ounce} in their bag.

== Filling ==

In a #large pan{}, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} over medium-high heat (for 4, we suggest a large, high-sided pan). Add ginger, garlic, and reserved remaining corn; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until corn begins to slightly char, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Carefully transfer corn mixture to #blender{} (reserve pan for use in Step 5). Add @crème fraîche{6%tablespoon} and @veggie stock concentrate{2}; blend until mostly smooth, scraping down the sides as needed, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Transfer blended corn mixture to bowl with reserved corn. Stir to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Wontons ==

Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Meanwhile, on a clean work surface, add 1/2 TBSP corn filling to the center of one @wonton wrappers{24} - repeat with remaining wrappers and corn filling to form 20 wontons (40 for 4 servings) (cover filled wontons and remaining wrappers with a damp #paper towel{} as you work to keep them from drying out).

Using your fingers, lightly brush edges of wrapper with water. Fold wrapper in half over filling to form a rectangle; pinch well to seal. Repeat with remaining wrappers.

> You'll have wonton wrappers left over—they freeze well for up to three months! Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and store in a freezer-friendly plastic bag.

== Coconut Curry Sauce ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Add onion and green beans. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion begins to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add half the @curry powder{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings); cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Add @coconut milk{1}(thoroughly shaken before opening) and @water{1/4%cup} (1/2 cup for 4). Stir in @Sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, half the cilantro, remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and juice from half the lime. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until curry is creamy and thickened slightly, ~{60-90%seconds}. Remove from heat (you'll add more to the pan in Step 6).

== Assembly ==

Once water is boiling, carefully add wontons to #pot{}. Stir. Cook until wontons are tender, ~{60-90%seconds}. Drain.

Transfer drained wontons to pan with curry sauce; gently stir until wontons are thoroughly coated in sauce.

> Cooked wontons are delicate—stir carefully to avoid breaking.

Divide sweet corn and ginger wontons between shallow #bowls{}; top with any remaining curry sauce from pan. Garnish with peanuts and remaining cilantro. Serve with a squeeze of lime juice.

> Like things spicy? Add your favorite hot sauce or chili flakes!